   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-d" mid="53" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="52"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>1. <FONT color=#086171>Meet your skill trainer NPC and select [Learn Skill].</FONT><BR>2. <FONT color=#086171>You must fulfill the minimum level requirements to learn skill.</FONT><BR>3. <FONT color=#086171>The skill level of the prerequisite skill needs to meet a certain level.</FONT><BR>4. <FONT color=#086171>You need skill points.</FONT><BR>5. <FONT color=#086171>You cannot exceed maximum skill points given to your particular job class.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-e" mid="55" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="54"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>
It may be a little complicated and difficult for users who are playing Dragon Nest for the first time, but Warp characters can attain skills easily.<BR>
First, shall we take a look at how to open the <FONT color=#a82424>skill window</FONT>?<BR>
Skill window's shortcut button is <FONT color=#a82424>[ K ]</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-f" mid="57" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="56"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>On the left side of the skill window are <FONT color=#387206>{user_nick}</FONT>'s jobs classified into different tabs in order. There are a total of 3 tabs of basic class, 1st job, and 2nd job.<BR>Each job class has its own skill tree.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-g" mid="64" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="63"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>
If you click <FONT color=#a82424>[ + ]</FONT> on the right side of the skill icons, you can increase the level of that particular skill by using <FONT color=#a82424>skill points</FONT>. Also, by right-clicking the skill icon, you can see the preview of the skill from the video played on the right side of the skill window.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-h" mid="81" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="80"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>
Now, let's try it hands on. <BR>When you finish this <FONT color=#a82424>Lesson</FONT>, you will be given a <FONT color=#a82424>skill initialisation item (1-day unlimited initialisation)</FONT> so try picking the skills as much as you want.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-1-skill_set" mid="59" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>[Learn Skill]</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="58"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>* You can open the skill window with <FONT color=#7e12d2>shortcut key [ K ].</FONT><BR>* <FONT color=#7e12d2>You can see a preview of the skill by right-clicking the skill icon.</FONT><BR>* <FONT color=#7e12d2>Click the flag and [ + ] button on the right side of the skill icons to learn and increase skill level.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-2-a" mid="67" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="65"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>How was it?<BR>It's not that difficult to learn skills, right?<BR>Now I shall tell you more basic things about skills before ending this <FONT color=#a82424>Lesson</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-2-b" mid="69" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="68"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>Skills are divided into <FONT color=#a82424>active</FONT> and <FONT color=#a82424>passive</FONT> skills.<BR>Active skills refer to skills that will be activated when you use the skills directly. On the other hand, passive skills refer to skills that are always activated and applied to characters.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-2-c" mid="71" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="70"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>If the skill icon's colour is yellow, it is a passive skill. If it is blue, it is an active skill. To use active skills, you have to register them into the <FONT color=#a82424>quick slot</FONT>.<BR>Quickslots are the <FONT color=#a82424>10 slots</FONT> at the bottom centre of the main screen, on the left and right side of the minimap.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n101_event_tracey-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n101_event_tracey-2-d" mid="76" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="72"><![CDATA[<html>$Warp Helper Tracy$<BR>Click the skill icon at the skill window and drag it to the quickslot to register. Afterwards, you can use the quickslot shortcut buttons <FONT color=#a82424>[1 ~ 0]</FONT> to use the skills.<BR>
* <FONT color=#7e12d2>Skills cannot be used in towns and can be used outside towns.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
